{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778982763961,"sessionID":"ses_1cc64459affeu3X9jgV7TXM1Y3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ujYl4TAEw6E2nkUfP4Hh2e1O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated `GO:0140597` (`protein carrier activity`) to the broader wording requested in the thread.\n+\n+The definition now reads: \"Directly binding to a protein and delivering it either to an acceptor molecule or to a specific location.\"\n+\n+The change has been committed locally and can be included in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This PR updates the textual definition for `GO:0140597` (`protein carrier activity`) in response to issue #31601.\n+\n+Change made:\n+\n+- Revised the definition from:\n+  `Binding to and carrying a protein to an acceptor molecule or to a specific location by moving along with the target protein.`\n+- To:\n+  `Directly binding to a protein and delivering it either to an acceptor molecule or to a specific location.`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- This follows the requested wording from the issue discussion, specifically to avoid the older, more restrictive phrasing.\n+- The revised text also aligns better with the wording already used in related carrier activity definitions elsewhere in GO (for example, lipid and ion/molecule carrier activity terms that use the same \"Directly binding ... and delivering it either to an acceptor molecule or to a specific location\" pattern).\n+- No logical axioms or hierarchy changes were needed for this issue; this is a textual clarification only.\n+\n+Checks completed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: Issue context reviewed and intent was clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Ran pre-edit validation checks relevant to definitions/namespaces\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Reviewed current stanzas for `GO:0140597` and related `GO:0140309`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Checked for relevant